snippet.textDisplay: Some misreporting going on here. Excel is capable of handling over 1 millions rows yes, but the problem wasn't that. The problem was they were using an old excel format XLS instead of CSV or XLSX. XLS is only capable of 65k rows where XLSX is capable of 1,048,576. CSV technically doesn't have a row limit but if used in excel it can only handle the 1,048,576 which is excel's current limit. Though the UK really should have used Power BI or Tableau instead of excel for this.
